Baidu Inc Proposes Debt Offering
Monday, 5 Nov 2012 05:46pm EST
Baidu Inc announced that it has filed an automatic shelf registration statement on Form F-3 with the United States Securities and Exchange Commission (the SEC), and a preliminary prospectus supplement under the registration statement, pursuant to which the Company proposes to sell senior notes which will be issued in two tranches. The Company intends to use a portion of the net proceeds from the offering to retire certain existing debt and the remainder for general corporate purposes. The joint bookrunners of the offering are J.P. Morgan Securities LLC and Goldman Sachs (Asia) L.L.C.Â 
